1 olive oil
1 beetroot
2 carrot
1 parsnip
1 Brown Onion
1 bag herbs
1 packet chicken thigh
½ tsp brown sugar
1 sachet Brown Mustard Seeds
1 bag Mixed Leaves
1 apple
2 clove garlic
1 sachet Mumbai Spice Blend
1 drizzle vinegar (white wine or red wine)
1 packet Greek-Style Yoghurt

• Preheat oven to 220°C/200°C fan-forced.
• Cut beetroot and parsnip into bite-sized
chunks. Cut some of the carrot (1 for 2 people /
2 for 4 people) into bite-sized chunks.
• Place chopped beetroot, parsnip and carrot on
a lined oven tray. Season with salt and drizzle
with olive oil. Toss to coat, spread out evenly,
then roast until tender, 25-30 minutes.

• Meanwhile, thinly slice onion. Finely chop garlic.
Thinly slice apple into wedges. Grate remaining
carrot. Pick and finely chop herbs.
• In a medium bowl, combine Mumbai spice
blend, the brown sugar and a drizzle of olive
oil, then season with salt and pepper.
• Add chicken thigh and turn to coat. Set aside.

• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil
over medium-high heat. Add onion and brown
mustard seeds, season, then cook, stirring
occasionally, until softened, 4-5 minutes.
• Add garlic and cook until fragrant, 1 minute.
Transfer to a large bowl.

• Return the frying pan to medium-high heat
with a drizzle of olive oil. Cook chicken until
browned, 2 minutes each side.
• Transfer chicken to a second lined oven tray and
bake until cooked through, 10-12 minutes.

TIP: Chicken is cooked through when it's no longer
pink inside.

• While the chicken is baking, combine apple,
grated carrot, mixed leaves and herbs in a large
bowl. Add a drizzle of vinegar and olive oil, then
toss to coat. Season to taste.

• Slice Mumbai chicken. Transfer roast root veggies
to the bowl with onion and mustard seeds and
toss to combine.
• Divide seeded roast root veggies, mixed salad
and Mumbai chicken between bowls.
• Top with Greek-style yoghurt to serve. Enjoy!